    "If not, then there is a Y ′ ⊑ G h(X) such that in the Boolean algebra associated with G's poset, Y ′ ∧ g[X] = ⊥.",
    "By Fact 4.44, h satisfies ⊑-back, so Y ′ ⊑ G h(X) implies that there is a Y ∈ (F b) p such that Y ⊑ (F b)p X and h(Y) ⊑ G Y ′."
